---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="8-Letter Words With X — MAXIMIZE, APPENDIX, ORTHODOX & FOXHOUND"
  description="Top 8-letter X words for Scrabble bingos. MAXIMIZE (28pts), FOXHOUND (22pts), APPENDIX (20pts), ORTHODOX (19pts). Strategy for X-tile bingo plays."
  keywords="8 letter words with x, maximize scrabble, appendix scrabble word, orthodox scrabble, foxhound scrabble, x bingo words, eight letter x words"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "8-Letter Words With X — MAXIMIZE, APPENDIX, ORTHODOX & FOXHOUND",
    "description": "Top 8-letter X words for Scrabble bingos. MAXIMIZE (28pts), FOXHOUND (22pts), APPENDIX (20pts), ORTHODOX (19pts). Strategy for X-tile bingo plays.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-29",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/8-letter-words-with-x" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "What 8-letter X words score highest in Scrabble?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "MAXIMIZE leads at 28 points (also contains Z). FOXHOUND scores 22 points, APPENDIX scores 20 points, and ORTHODOX scores 19 points. With the 50-point bingo bonus, these reach 69-78 total points." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Is FOXHOUND a valid Scrabble word?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Yes, FOXHOUND is valid in both TWL and SOWPODS dictionaries, scoring 22 points (F=4, O=1, X=8, H=4, O=1, U=1, N=1, D=2). It combines the X tile (8pts) with F (4pts) and H (4pts) for a strong bingo play." } },
      { "@type": "Question", "name": "Should I save X for an 8-letter bingo or play it short?", "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "It depends on your rack. If you have X plus 6 common tiles that form an 8-letter word, hold for the bingo (58-78 points). If not, play X on a premium square for 24-48 points immediately rather than waiting for tiles that may never come." } }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">Bingos</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">8-Letter Words With X — MAXIMIZE, APPENDIX, ORTHODOX & FOXHOUND</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-29">June 29, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        The X tile is worth 8 points — second only to Q and Z. When you can incorporate X into an 8-letter bingo, you're looking at 69+ points in a single play. These words combine the power of X with common tiles that are easy to draw, making them realistic bingo targets.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 Top Scorer</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MAXIMIZE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">28 points base + 50 bingo bonus = 78 total</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The ultimate X-word bingo. Also contains Z (10pts), making it the highest-scoring common 8-letter word. M(3)+A(1)+X(8)+I(1)+M(3)+I(1)+Z(10)+E(1).</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 8-Letter X Words</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🏆 MAXIMIZE — 28 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Contains X(8) + Z(10). Double premium tiles in one bingo. 78 with bonus.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">🦊 FOXHOUND — 22 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">F(4)+O(1)+X(8)+H(4)+O(1)+U(1)+N(1)+D(2). Three 4-point tiles stacked.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">📎 APPENDIX — 20 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A(1)+P(3)+P(3)+E(1)+N(1)+D(2)+I(1)+X(8). X at the end for clean placement.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">⛪ ORTHODOX — 19 pts</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">O(1)+R(1)+T(1)+H(4)+O(1)+D(2)+O(1)+X(8). Uses three O tiles with X and H.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">X Position Patterns</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Placement Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">X appears in different positions: <span class="text-white font-medium">middle</span> (MAXIMIZE, FOXHOUND, ORTHODOX) and <span class="text-white font-medium">end</span> (APPENDIX). End-position X words hook easily onto existing board words extending rightward.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Bingo Strategy With X</h2>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">APPENDIX hooks to board endings:</span> If there's a word ending near the edge, APPENDIX can extend through an existing letter. The X at position 8 means it lands at the far end — often on premium squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">FOXHOUND uses easy tiles:</span> Apart from X, every tile in FOXHOUND is common (F, O, H, O, U, N, D). If you hold X and see these letters forming, think bingo rather than short-play dump.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">When NOT to hold X:</span> If your rack is X plus awkward consonants (Q, K, W, V), don't wait. Play AX, EX, OX on a premium square for quick 20-30 points and refresh your rack.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">78 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MAXIMIZE</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">72 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">FOXHOUND</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">70 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">APPENDIX</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-amber-400">69 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">ORTHODOX</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/8-letter-words-with-z/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">8-Letter Words With Z — MAXIMIZE, ORGANIZE & More</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-starting-with-x/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words Starting With X — XYLOPHONE, XENON & More</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-x-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best X Words in Scrabble — Complete Scoring Guide</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-blue-800/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Try our free Scrabble Word Finder — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-400 text-gray-950 text-sm font-semibold transition-colors">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
